# Expo Native UI and Theming

## UI stack

- Build UI with **Expo native UI** only: prefer `@expo/ui` when used in the project, and Expoâ€™s Compose/SwiftUI-backed APIs (e.g. `expo-router/unstable-native-tabs` `NativeTabs`, `expo-symbols`).
- Do not introduce custom JS-only tab bars, generic third-party UI kits, or non-Expo native components when an Expo native equivalent exists.

## Platform-specific files

- Use **platform-specific extensions** so each platform gets the right implementation:
  - `.ios.tsx` / `.android.tsx` for native-only code.
  - `.native.tsx` for shared iOS + Android, `.web.tsx` for web.
- In `src/app/`, a non-platform file must exist for each route (e.g. `about.tsx`) so deep linking stays universal; add `about.ios.tsx`, `about.web.tsx`, etc. as overrides.
- Outside `src/app/`, use the same extensions (e.g. `components/app-tabs.ios.tsx`, `components/app-tabs.android.tsx`, `components/app-tabs.web.tsx`) and import by base name; Metro resolves the correct file.

```tsx
// âś… GOOD: platform-specific components
// components/app-tabs.ios.tsx, app-tabs.android.tsx, app-tabs.web.tsx
import AppTabs from '@/components/app-tabs';

// âś… GOOD: route with fallback for deep links
// app/about.tsx (default) + app/about.web.tsx
```

## Theming (native colors)

- Use the **Expo Router Color API** for native colors: `import { Color } from 'expo-router'`.
- Prefer semantic colors so light/dark and (on Android) dynamic color work:
  - **iOS:** `Color.ios.systemBackground`, `Color.ios.label`, `Color.ios.secondaryLabel`, etc.
  - **Android:** `Color.android.dynamic.surface`, `Color.android.dynamic.onSurface`, or `Color.android.material.*` for static roles.
- Call `useColorScheme()` in any component that uses these colors so it re-renders when the system theme changes.
- For cross-platform or web, use `Platform.select` with a `default` (e.g. app theme object) when `Color` has no namespace.

```tsx
// âś… GOOD: theming with Expo Router Color API
import { Color } from 'expo-router';
import { View, Text, useColorScheme, Platform } from 'react-native';

function ThemedScreen() {
  useColorScheme();
  const bg = Platform.select({
    ios: Color.ios.systemBackground,
    android: Color.android.dynamic.surface,
    default: '#fff',
  });
  return <View style={{ backgroundColor: bg }}><Text>Hello</Text></View>;
}
```

## Summary

- Expo native UI only (e.g. @expo/ui, NativeTabs, expo-symbols).
- Platform-specific files: `.ios.tsx`, `.android.tsx`, `.native.tsx`, `.web.tsx`.
- Theming: `Color` from `expo-router` + `useColorScheme()` for theme updates.
